This paper deals with the intersection of category theory and type theory, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The paper specifically discusses locally cartesian closed categories and Martin-Lof type theories, which are concepts that are commonly studied in the sub-fields of logic (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), category theory (cs.CT), and theoretical computer science (cs.TC). Additionally, the use of categories with families as a substitute for syntactic Martin-Lof type theories suggests a connection to the sub-field of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
